---
description: Frontend guidance for the Next.js app
globs:
    - "src/app/**/*"
    - "src/components/**/*"
    - "src/contexts/**/*"
    - "src/lib/**/*"
alwaysApply: false
---

Use React, Next.js App Router, strict TypeScript, accessible controls, stable
responsive layouts, localized copy, and existing Tailwind conventions. Keep
wallet logic isolated to wagmi/Reown helpers and avoid exposing non-`NEXT_PUBLIC_*`
values to the browser. Run `cd src && npx tsc --noEmit`, `npm run lint:frontend`,
relevant Jest/Playwright tests, and the production build (`npm run build:frontend`)
after frontend changes. Enforce `docs/QUALITY-STANDARDS.md`: keep React Doctor at
100/100 (`npm run doctor`) and do not merge below it; maintain Lighthouse 95+ in
every category (Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices, SEO) before
deployment and target 100 where achievable; hold the line on accessibility,
security, re-render/performance, and bundle health; never introduce unused code;
and investigate and resolve new warnings at their root cause instead of
suppressing them.
